The only criteria in promotion consideration at my university is grant income. Alternatively, if one gets an offer from another university then promotion is likely. Otherwise, forget about it. Grant acquisition should be removed from the criteria (and indeed, it is not explicit in theme at my uni -- but is directly linked to promotion, even more tightly than publication). It is a poor tool given the disparities in funding availability and processes across disciplines and funding bodies, not to mention geographical regions. Conversely collegiality, which is among the criteria, should matter more - currently it operates  on promotion only in name and not in fact.
